# Data Access & Validation (Next.js)

## Query & Mutation Helpers

- **All database interactions** (reads and writes) must go through **helper functions** defined in `src/db/queries/`.
  - Do **not** call Drizzle directly inside Server Components or Server Actions — always delegate to a query/mutation helper.
  - Organise helpers by domain (e.g. `src/db/queries/decks.ts`, `src/db/queries/cards.ts`).
  - Each helper file exports typed async functions (e.g. `getDecksByUserId`, `createDeck`, `deleteDeck`).
- **Read helpers** (selects) live in `src/db/queries/` and are called from Server Components or server-only utilities.
- **Mutation helpers** (insert / update / delete) also live in `src/db/queries/` and are called exclusively from Server Actions.

## Data Retrieval (Reads)

- Must be done via **Server Components** (or server-only utilities called by Server Components).
- Server Components call the appropriate helper from `src/db/queries/` — do not fetch DB data in Client Components.

## Data Mutations (Writes)

- Any **insert / update / delete** must be triggered via **Server Actions** (`"use server"`).
- Server Actions call the appropriate mutation helper from `src/db/queries/`.
- Do not write to the DB from Client Components, API routes, or client-side fetch calls.

## Validation

- **All incoming data** to mutations must be validated with **Zod** inside the Server Action before calling the query helper.
- Every Server Action must accept a **typed object** input derived from Zod (e.g. `type Input = z.infer<typeof schema>`).
- **Do not use `FormData` as the input type** for Server Actions. Convert/shape client form values into a typed object, then validate with Zod.

## Still follow existing rules

- DB access uses Drizzle schema/types from [`src/db/schema.ts`](mdc:src/db/schema.ts)
- User scoping/ownership enforced via Clerk (`userId`) — always pass `userId` into query helpers and filter by it
